article_title: U.S. Import Prices Down 0.5% in October
article_text:
WASHINGTON—Prices for imported goods fell for the fourth straight month in October, highlighting the drag on inflation from cheap oil, a strong dollar and slow overseas growth.

Import prices dropped 0.5% from the prior month, the Labor Department said Tuesday. Economists surveyed by The Wall Street Journal had expected a 0.1% decline.
